    <!-- Finding 4: Inline Styles Issue -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="finding-4-inline-styles">🔴 Finding 4: Inline Styles Compliance Gap (CRITICAL FINDING)</h2>

        <div class="alert alert-warning" style="background: var(--caution-bg, #fff3cd); border: 1px solid var(--caution-color, #ffc107);">
            <h3>❌ COMPLIANCE ISSUE IDENTIFIED</h3>
            <p><strong>Total Inline Styles Found:</strong> <strong>1,936 style="..." attributes</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Affected Files:</strong> <strong>56 documentation .tt files</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Estimated vs. Actual:</strong> Initial estimate was 1,527 (67% underestimated - actual is 409 attributes higher)</p>
            <p><strong>Impact:</strong> Hardcoded colors and spacing make it difficult to maintain consistent themes and apply future CSS changes globally.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Why This Matters</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Maintainability:</strong> Changing a color scheme requires editing 1,936 individual attributes instead of 1 CSS variable</li>
            <li><strong>Theme Consistency:</strong> Per-site themes can't override hardcoded inline styles</li>
            <li><strong>CSS Refactoring:</strong> Future redesigns are much more difficult with inline styles scattered throughout templates</li>
            <li><strong>Code Quality:</strong> Violates CSS best practices (separation of concerns)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Example of the Problem</h3>
        <pre><code>❌ BEFORE (Current - inline styles):
&lt;div style="background: #d4edda; padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; margin: 20px 0; border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color, #28a745);"&gt;

✅ AFTER (Refactored - CSS variables):
&lt;div style="background: var(--success-bg); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: var(--border-radius); margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0; border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color);"&gt;</code></pre>
    </div>

